1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3882 By: Cantrell
4
5
AS INTRODUCED
6
An Act relating to appropriations; making certain
7 appropriation to the Oklahoma Department of
Transportation; stating use of funds appropriated;
8 providing an effective date; and declaring an
emergency.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma
13 Department of Transportation from any monies not otherwise
14 appropriated from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for
15 the fiscal year ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Ten Million Dollars
16 ($10,000,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to perform
17 the duties imposed upon the Oklahoma Department of Transportation
18 for lake and industrial access grants imposed by law.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
20 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
21 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
22 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
